WEBVTT

00:05.047 --> 00:07.425
WHILE THIS STORY IS BASED
ON ACTUAL EVENTS,

00:07.508 --> 00:10.970
CERTAIN CHARACTERS, INCIDENTS,
AND DIALOGUE WERE FICTIONALIZED.

00:11.053 --> 00:15.015
ANY SIMILARITY TO ANY PERSON,
LIVING OR DEAD, IS FOR DRAMATIC PURPOSES.

00:19.145 --> 00:21.230
FALKLAND ISLANDS, ENGLAND

00:21.313 --> 00:23.315
MALVINAS ISLANDS, ARGENTINA

02:02.414 --> 02:04.583
MARADONA:
BLESSED DREAM

02:04.917 --> 02:06.252
MACHINE

02:13.717 --> 02:15.803
- Wait here, please.
- Hello.

02:15.886 --> 02:18.514
Will you let the doctor know
we've brought Coppola in?

02:19.431 --> 02:21.559
<i>So, what you're saying is,</i>

02:21.642 --> 02:25.271
<i>that at the time</i>
<i>of Mr. Maradona's decompensation,</i>

02:25.729 --> 02:28.190
only you and the owner of the house
were present,

02:28.274 --> 02:30.818
- and no one else.
- Exactly, Your Honor.

02:31.610 --> 02:35.072
Claudia Villafañe,
Mr. Maradona's wife, was not there.

02:35.155 --> 02:37.116
Well, yes, she was.

02:37.324 --> 02:40.369
She was asleep with the girls
in the main house.

02:41.745 --> 02:47.001
Because Diego and his wife are,
let's say, separated.

02:47.084 --> 02:49.712
Well, they're still together,
but separated.

02:50.170 --> 02:53.757
She was there
because they decided to spend

02:54.216 --> 02:55.718
the holidays as a family.

02:57.678 --> 02:59.221
Let's see, Mr. Coppola.

03:00.097 --> 03:02.182
A witness testified

03:03.058 --> 03:06.729
that there was a third person
in the guest house.

03:08.731 --> 03:13.110
<i>A male, between 45 and 50 years old,</i>

03:14.194 --> 03:19.325
<i>black hair, brown eyes, 5'6".</i>

03:19.408 --> 03:20.784
<i>A third person?</i>

03:21.160 --> 03:23.245
Sorry, Your Honor, with all due respect.

03:23.329 --> 03:27.041
I don't know who your witness is,

03:27.917 --> 03:33.005
but it sounds like they might've had
one too many on New Year's Eve.

03:33.297 --> 03:36.008
Something tells me
that if we look in the magazines

03:36.091 --> 03:38.552
for photos of Mr. Maradona's last stay,

03:38.636 --> 03:41.430
we'll find this third person.

03:41.805 --> 03:44.183
And that the witness will recognize him.

03:45.392 --> 03:46.810
Save me the paperwork.

03:50.439 --> 03:51.982
Carlos Ferro Viera.

03:54.318 --> 03:58.072
And why did you omit
his presence in your statement?

03:59.031 --> 04:01.283
<i>Because Ferro is a friend of Diego's</i>

04:01.367 --> 04:04.495
<i>who, let's say</i>
<i>he's not very well thought of,</i>

04:04.578 --> 04:06.580
<i>to avoid a media scandal.</i>

04:06.664 --> 04:08.165
WANTED
CARLOS FERRO VIERA

04:08.248 --> 04:10.501
<i>Sure. But this is the law.</i>

04:10.960 --> 04:14.630
<i>Where do Mr. Ferro Viera</i>
<i>and Mr. Maradona know each other from?</i>

04:14.713 --> 04:16.173
<i>I introduced them.</i>

04:16.256 --> 04:18.050
<i>I met Ferro when</i>

04:19.385 --> 04:22.304
I was arrested in my country.

04:22.638 --> 04:25.182
On a made-up, bogus charge.

04:25.265 --> 04:28.727
For the record,
I was declared completely innocent

04:28.811 --> 04:30.771
by justice system in my country.

04:31.480 --> 04:34.191
We could say that Mr. Ferro Viera is

04:34.274 --> 04:37.778
the one who provides cocaine
to your client here in Uruguay.

04:37.903 --> 04:39.279
I don't know.

04:39.655 --> 04:44.159
I thank God
I'm not at all involved with drugs

04:44.243 --> 04:49.373
and, as everyone knows,
Diego's in the process of recovery.

04:49.915 --> 04:52.459
Is Ferro Viera still here
in Punta del Este?

04:54.169 --> 04:56.463
I have no idea, Your Honor.

04:57.381 --> 05:00.009
I haven't been in the house
since Diego was hospitalized,

05:00.092 --> 05:04.304
not even to change my clothes.
I've been with Diego and his family.

05:04.388 --> 05:09.476
With all due respect, Your Honor,
I'd like to wrap this up.

05:10.019 --> 05:13.439
These are crucial moments and I need

05:14.481 --> 05:17.109
to be by my friend's side at the hospital.

05:21.572 --> 05:22.740
Next.

05:32.166 --> 05:35.044
DEPARTURE GATE

05:47.765 --> 05:50.559
I have a question.
I'm trying to figure out who this is.

05:51.185 --> 05:52.269
I can't place him.

05:52.352 --> 05:53.771
- Who is he?
- I don't know.

05:54.104 --> 05:56.106
- I have no idea.
- No?

05:56.190 --> 05:57.483
Do you know this guy?

05:58.776 --> 05:59.693
Yes.

05:59.777 --> 06:01.028
- You do?
- So do you.

06:01.737 --> 06:05.240
- No, I have no idea who this is.
- Yes, you do.

06:05.532 --> 06:08.660
Imagine him without glasses
and shorter hair.

06:09.787 --> 06:13.749
You almost have it.
Put some gray in his beard.

06:15.125 --> 06:16.043
Think.

06:16.752 --> 06:17.669
No!

06:18.420 --> 06:20.589
What an idiot! I couldn't saw it.

06:20.672 --> 06:22.466
You can tell it's Ricardo.

06:23.884 --> 06:26.345
You'll see a lot of photos
of them from that time.

06:26.428 --> 06:28.597
When Maradona played in Europe,

06:28.680 --> 06:30.349
Ricardo was his press officer.

06:30.432 --> 06:32.601
I didn't know they had a relationship.

06:32.684 --> 06:34.394
He was cold when he broke the news.

06:34.478 --> 06:36.605
They ended on really bad terms.

06:36.688 --> 06:38.607
Nobody knows what really happened,

06:38.690 --> 06:41.777
but as much as I love Diego,
I can tell you one thing.

06:41.860 --> 06:46.365
No friend, press agent, or manager
has lasted more than five years with him.

06:46.448 --> 06:49.535
Right. Well, thank you very much.

06:50.536 --> 06:51.870
- Can I have it?
- Okay.

06:51.954 --> 06:52.788
Thank you.

06:54.581 --> 06:57.793
RIO DE JANEIRO, BRAZIL.

06:57.876 --> 06:59.586
I don't know any Maradona.

06:59.670 --> 07:01.505
Maradona doesn't exist here.

07:01.588 --> 07:03.882
Because you don't know
anything about soccer.

07:03.966 --> 07:07.594
We've won three World Cups.
And you? Just one.

07:07.678 --> 07:09.346
That was fixed by the military.

07:09.429 --> 07:11.348
Watch what you say, Brazilian.

07:11.849 --> 07:14.184
The 1978 champions are friends of mine.

07:14.643 --> 07:16.895
If you make me mad
and I'll get out of the cab.

07:16.979 --> 07:19.398
Get out here in the favela and shout,

07:19.815 --> 07:21.775
"Argentina is better than Brazil.

07:21.859 --> 07:24.278
Brazilians don't know
anything about soccer."

07:24.361 --> 07:27.906
They'll come down from the hill
and turn you into a girl.

07:27.990 --> 07:29.032
What did he say?

07:29.116 --> 07:31.076
If you get out here and shout

07:31.160 --> 07:34.079
that we're better than Brazil in a favela,

07:34.163 --> 07:36.206
they'll turn you into a girl.

07:36.290 --> 07:38.584
I take it back, I'm not getting out.

07:38.667 --> 07:41.837
We're here to do a special edition
for a sports magazine,

07:41.920 --> 07:44.506
because Diego's
the best player in Argentina.

07:44.590 --> 07:46.675
They say he'll be bigger than Pelé.

07:46.758 --> 07:47.843
Bigger than Pelé?

07:48.010 --> 07:50.345
So, Maradona is from another planet?

07:51.305 --> 07:52.222
Yes.

08:01.148 --> 08:02.274
How much is it?

08:02.357 --> 08:03.317
Twenty.

08:06.111 --> 08:07.321
Diego!

08:09.114 --> 08:10.240
Go.

08:11.783 --> 08:14.453
- An autograph?
- Yes, of course.

08:18.457 --> 08:21.210
Gentlemen, welcome. Please, come with me.

08:25.339 --> 08:27.216
Maybe he's taking a nap?

08:27.758 --> 08:29.968
Come, wait here quietly.

08:30.052 --> 08:32.012
- Please.
- Gentlemen.

08:33.889 --> 08:35.849
- Hello.
- What a pleasure.

08:35.933 --> 08:38.227
Thank you so much for having us.

08:38.310 --> 08:40.103
There's no need for introductions.

08:40.187 --> 08:41.647
Diego, how are you?

08:41.855 --> 08:43.273
Nice to meet you.

08:45.567 --> 08:47.361
What are you doing?

08:47.444 --> 08:50.072
Just making sure I'm not dreaming, sir.

08:50.614 --> 08:53.450
I've been following Diego
since he started,

08:53.533 --> 08:55.327
but I've never seen him this excited.

08:55.410 --> 08:57.996
Not even when he won
the Youth Championship.

08:58.914 --> 09:01.166
It's been two years since I retired.

09:01.250 --> 09:02.709
I miss the fans.

09:03.585 --> 09:08.674
The buzz and the smell of the grass.

09:08.757 --> 09:11.134
<i>I'm revealing who I am</i>

09:11.218 --> 09:15.097
<i>And I'm being who I can be</i>
<i>I throw myself into the world</i>

09:15.180 --> 09:17.557
<i>Walking everywhere</i>

09:17.641 --> 09:20.310
<i>And by the natural law of encounters</i>

09:20.394 --> 09:22.396
<i>I give and take a little bit more</i>

09:22.479 --> 09:25.065
<i>I use my eyes, naked or spectacled</i>

09:25.148 --> 09:26.692
<i>Past, present</i>

09:26.775 --> 09:29.820
<i>I participate by being</i>
<i>A mystery of this planet...</i>

09:30.696 --> 09:34.032
I like you very much, Dieguito. Look.

09:39.788 --> 09:41.039
Look, Dieguito.

09:41.123 --> 09:42.207
Hello.

09:54.845 --> 09:56.138
Sir.

09:59.224 --> 10:01.810
- May I ask for your autograph?
- Of course.

10:02.436 --> 10:03.812
<i>Take care of yourself</i>

10:03.895 --> 10:06.315
<i>and always stay away from bad company.</i>

10:06.606 --> 10:08.400
Healthy mind and body.

10:09.985 --> 10:11.361
Thank you, King.

10:11.445 --> 10:13.572
- Shall we take a picture?
- Sure.

10:16.742 --> 10:18.368
This manual is in Portuguese.

10:19.244 --> 10:20.829
What did you expect, Arabic?

10:20.912 --> 10:22.622
I bought it in Brazil, dummy.

10:22.706 --> 10:26.543
I heard you can't watch it for long,
because it ruins your sight.

10:26.626 --> 10:29.463
If we keep going like this,
we won't see any.

10:29.546 --> 10:31.715
Out the way. Leave it to me.

10:31.798 --> 10:34.593
- Thank God you play soccer.
- Go ahead.

10:34.676 --> 10:35.886
How does it look?

10:35.969 --> 10:38.180
They haven't installed the antenna yet.

10:38.263 --> 10:40.974
Tell me something nice
about your trip to Brazil.

10:41.058 --> 10:43.560
Besides Pelé, what else did you see?

10:43.643 --> 10:47.105
The beaches have white sand
and warm water.

10:47.606 --> 10:51.860
And the women all wear these tiny bikinis.

10:51.943 --> 10:53.779
Fat women cover themselves up here.

10:53.862 --> 10:57.199
But there, they're all half-naked,
showing their asses.

10:58.283 --> 10:59.409
All of them.

10:59.493 --> 11:01.244
Tall ones, thin ones,

11:01.328 --> 11:03.038
- short ones.
- Disgusting.

11:03.538 --> 11:07.167
- I said something nice, not that filth.
- I think it's nice.

11:07.292 --> 11:08.543
Is that so?

11:08.627 --> 11:13.048
You wouldn't mind me walking around
in nothing but a string?

11:15.342 --> 11:17.010
Are you crazy, Mom?

11:18.220 --> 11:20.263
Tell Morsa about where Pelé lives.

11:20.347 --> 11:22.015
He lives in a mansion.

11:22.099 --> 11:25.268
Yes, a huge house.
About 30 times bigger than this one.

11:25.435 --> 11:28.688
And there were girls
sunbathing in the pool.

11:29.022 --> 11:31.108
His girlfriend is a beautiful blonde.

11:31.191 --> 11:34.569
- A real blonde.
- So you prefer blondes over brunettes?

11:34.653 --> 11:37.739
No, are you crazy? No way.

11:37.948 --> 11:42.494
I like brunettes,
with straight hair and bangs.

11:42.702 --> 11:46.081
That's it. Okay, Chitoro.
Move the antenna.

11:47.082 --> 11:49.126
- There?
- Like that, Chitoro! That's it!

11:49.209 --> 11:50.794
Don't touch anything else.

11:55.465 --> 11:56.716
Dad!

11:57.092 --> 12:00.011
What? What are you looking at?
Look at the colors.

12:00.095 --> 12:02.347
Wait till they see you
in a Boca jersey, kid.

12:02.431 --> 12:04.307
- With the blue and gold.
- Okay.

12:31.668 --> 12:33.378
I'm throwing the ball to him.

12:35.464 --> 12:39.426
My boy'd never miss a chance

12:41.511 --> 12:43.180
to head the ball.

12:44.931 --> 12:47.350
You always call him that? "My boy"?

12:54.357 --> 12:56.735
And he's about to turn 40.

12:57.903 --> 12:59.362
But time...

13:01.239 --> 13:02.741
is different for him.

13:05.619 --> 13:07.913
Forty years of his life is...

13:09.706 --> 13:13.668
I don't know how many lives
for an ordinary person.

13:15.629 --> 13:18.548
The trips around the world
that my boy took.

13:19.841 --> 13:22.552
And so many trips inside his head.

13:23.053 --> 13:25.555
Because it's not easy to be in his shoes.

13:28.266 --> 13:29.643
He held on...

13:31.311 --> 13:32.729
and he held on.

13:34.856 --> 13:37.776
And I'm sure he'll keep holding on.

13:39.319 --> 13:42.697
My children, Lalo and Huguito,

13:43.031 --> 13:45.450
already knew that when they were little.

13:45.951 --> 13:47.077
It's on film.

13:48.495 --> 13:52.165
As Diego's brothers,
they were interviewed once.

13:52.999 --> 13:55.001
The reporter asked Huguito,

13:55.085 --> 13:58.088
"When you grow up, you'll be like Diego?"

13:59.589 --> 14:01.716
And he said, very innocently,

14:02.467 --> 14:04.970
"I don't think I'll ever be like him.

14:06.096 --> 14:08.306
Because my brother is a Martian.

14:09.224 --> 14:10.934
There's no question about it."

14:11.017 --> 14:12.310
And that statement...

14:15.313 --> 14:17.107
has always been true.

14:17.190 --> 14:21.319
As if Huguito had had a vision.

14:27.951 --> 14:31.621
Many have already
given my son up for dead.

14:35.000 --> 14:36.543
But I have faith in him.

14:39.671 --> 14:41.464
Because he's a Martian.

14:44.092 --> 14:45.844
There's no question about it.

14:49.055 --> 14:50.223
Excuse me.

15:04.863 --> 15:06.448
Wake up, son.

15:09.618 --> 15:11.953
You have a game today, did you forget?

15:16.374 --> 15:17.584
Son.

15:17.709 --> 15:21.171
- No, I need to sleep a little more.
- Good morning, handsome.

15:21.463 --> 15:22.797
Wake up.

15:25.675 --> 15:26.843
Hello, honey.

15:26.926 --> 15:29.012
- Hello.
- Claudia brought you the paper.

15:29.095 --> 15:31.431
You can read
what they say about the game.

15:32.140 --> 15:34.976
No kiss for mommy? Good morning.

15:37.145 --> 15:39.564
What does it say? Look.

15:41.024 --> 15:44.527
Gatti is so rude.
How can he say this?

15:44.611 --> 15:45.528
What did he do?

15:46.196 --> 15:48.156
He's just mean.

15:51.201 --> 15:52.452
Chubby?

15:54.245 --> 15:57.582
- He says I'm chubby.
- No, honey. You're not chubby.

15:58.208 --> 16:00.043
You need to eat.

16:00.418 --> 16:03.463
Daddy will be upset,
because he loves El Loco.

16:03.713 --> 16:05.340
What a fucking old asshole.

16:06.633 --> 16:07.717
Your daddy?

16:07.801 --> 16:09.886
No, Ma. Gatti.

16:10.470 --> 16:12.347
I don't get why he criticizes you.

16:12.430 --> 16:14.808
You were teammates on the national team.

16:14.933 --> 16:16.893
Who does he think he is?

16:18.061 --> 16:20.480
He never stops giving away stupid goals.

16:21.856 --> 16:23.775
You shouldn't have brought him this.

16:23.942 --> 16:26.945
Look at the bad mood
he's in now because of you.

16:27.195 --> 16:28.446
Let's go.

16:29.239 --> 16:31.408
Let him have his breakfast in peace.

16:31.950 --> 16:33.702
- Come on.
- Okay.

16:35.078 --> 16:37.497
I won't score just one goal
against this asshole.

16:37.580 --> 16:40.250
I'm gonna score four. Four.

16:44.504 --> 16:46.131
We'll see who's chubby.

16:48.925 --> 16:50.009
What did he say?

16:50.760 --> 16:52.303
He's gonna score four.

16:57.767 --> 16:59.769
Don't look at me like that.

16:59.853 --> 17:01.438
The press loves to stir things up.

17:01.521 --> 17:02.981
Why would I say that?

17:07.694 --> 17:09.112
I'll get four past you today.

17:09.988 --> 17:11.364
I promised my folks.

17:11.448 --> 17:14.451
Four against me, kid?
And they called me crazy.

17:14.534 --> 17:17.746
<i>A penalty for Argentinos Juniors,</i>
<i>there goes Diego, goal!</i>

17:18.121 --> 17:19.873
<i>Goal!</i>

17:19.956 --> 17:23.543
<i>Free kick for Argentinos Juniors,</i>
<i>Diego hit it... Super goal!</i>

17:23.626 --> 17:24.836
<i>Goal!</i>

17:25.128 --> 17:27.547
<i>Boca's ahead 3-2,</i>
<i>Argentinos looks to tie.</i>

17:27.630 --> 17:30.842
<i>Pasculi to Diego, goal!</i>

17:30.925 --> 17:35.513
<i>Don't tell me you're scoring again.</i>
<i>There goes Diego, goal!</i>

17:35.597 --> 17:40.059
<i>Goal!</i>

17:41.060 --> 17:42.604
Watch it, asshole.

17:42.687 --> 17:46.107
Lucky you.
If I'd been on a diet, I'd have scored 8.

17:46.399 --> 17:47.859
Diego, how are you?

17:47.942 --> 17:51.321
What can you say after this great victory
for Argentinos Juniors?

17:51.404 --> 17:53.448
<i>It was a good game,</i>

17:53.656 --> 17:57.744
<i>with lots of goals and I hope</i>
<i>that the Argentinos fans enjoyed it</i>

17:57.827 --> 17:59.287
<i>as much as the Boca fans.</i>

17:59.370 --> 18:02.123
<i>Hear that?</i>
<i>They're giving you a standing ovation.</i>

18:02.207 --> 18:04.751
<i>You don't hear that often</i>
<i>for a rival player.</i>

18:04.834 --> 18:05.877
<i>Diego! Diego!</i>

18:05.960 --> 18:09.589
<i>My dad's a Boca fan.</i>

18:10.048 --> 18:13.718
<i>And he must be sad</i>
<i>that they were eliminated,</i>

18:13.802 --> 18:15.887
<i>but this will make him feel better.</i>

18:15.970 --> 18:17.597
<i>-Thank you.</i>
<i>-Thank you, Diego.</i>

18:17.680 --> 18:19.641
<i>That was Diego Armando Maradona,</i>

18:19.724 --> 18:21.518
<i>captain of the Argentinos Juniors.</i>

18:21.768 --> 18:24.479
<i>-And for the first time in history...</i>
- There he is.

18:24.562 --> 18:25.772
<i>...a contract signing</i>

18:25.855 --> 18:28.608
<i>-is broadcast live on television.</i>
- So cute in his suit.

18:28.691 --> 18:31.820
<i>Apart from Maradona</i>
<i>and the other players involved,</i>

18:32.153 --> 18:36.449
<i>Jorge Cyterszpiler,</i>
<i>Diego's agent, is here,</i>

18:36.533 --> 18:39.494
<i>and Guillermo Coppola,</i>
<i>manager of the Boca players</i>

18:39.577 --> 18:42.664
<i>who will now go</i>
<i>to Argentinos Juniors as part of the deal.</i>

18:43.289 --> 18:45.375
<i>What would you like to say, Diego?</i>

18:45.458 --> 18:46.876
<i>I'm very happy.</i>

18:47.293 --> 18:50.839
<i>I'll be forever grateful</i>
<i>to the Argentinos fans</i>

18:50.922 --> 18:52.966
<i>and I'll carry them in my heart.</i>

18:53.383 --> 18:57.053
<i>And to the Boca fans,</i>
<i>especially to my old man,</i>

18:58.513 --> 19:00.348
<i>I hope I won't disappoint you.</i>

19:00.431 --> 19:03.726
- He mentioned me.
<i>-Bye, Argentinos. Hello, Boca.</i>

19:07.814 --> 19:09.482
He mentioned me.

19:13.361 --> 19:17.115
How does it feel to sign
a $4 million contract

19:17.198 --> 19:21.202
when the country's going through
an unprecedented economic crisis?

19:21.578 --> 19:25.748
I don't handle the numbers, guys.
Talk to Rengo about that.

19:26.541 --> 19:27.959
My business is soccer,

19:28.042 --> 19:31.629
and giving joy to the people
that really need it right now.

19:31.838 --> 19:34.883
When you're poor,
sometimes your only joy

19:34.966 --> 19:36.968
is when your team wins on Sunday.

19:37.760 --> 19:39.762
Don't forget that's where I come from.

19:39.846 --> 19:42.515
We used to have so many leaks
