44:05.018 --> 44:07.520
He is asking me
to give him an apartment?

44:07.604 --> 44:11.733
Sure, apartments, houses,
medicine, clothes.

44:11.816 --> 44:14.611
What the hell is wrong with them?
They're crazy!

44:18.823 --> 44:20.450
Calm down, honey.

44:21.076 --> 44:23.411
What the press says doesn't matter.

44:24.454 --> 44:25.372
It doesn't matter.

44:32.587 --> 44:34.547
There it is.

44:35.423 --> 44:36.883
I've got it.

44:37.384 --> 44:41.054
Come on. Here, hold it. Firmly.

44:42.680 --> 44:43.932
With both hands.

44:44.766 --> 44:46.226
Patience.

44:46.309 --> 44:49.979
You need patience to reel it in.
That's how you lose a dorado.

44:50.522 --> 44:53.400
Higher up, here. Hold it.

45:15.547 --> 45:17.632
I'm sure they're bitching about me.

45:19.342 --> 45:20.802
Especially Menotti.

45:22.137 --> 45:25.557
Why didn't you talk to him?
He could give you some good advice.

45:31.062 --> 45:33.857
Sometimes I want to disappear
off the face of the earth.

45:36.734 --> 45:39.028
I don't know what people want from me.

45:41.489 --> 45:44.409
It's like I have to apologize
for everything I have.

45:45.368 --> 45:47.662
You've sacrificed a lot.

45:47.745 --> 45:49.956
- When we were...
- Hello.

45:51.958 --> 45:54.169
What the fuck are you doing here, Ricardo?

45:54.252 --> 45:57.922
Sorry, Diego.
I know I'm interrupting your vacation,

45:58.006 --> 45:59.507
but people are getting crazy.

45:59.591 --> 46:02.969
They want to know if you're retiring,
what you're up to.

46:03.052 --> 46:04.971
You're out of your mind.

46:05.430 --> 46:07.390
Come on, let's talk for a minute.

46:07.474 --> 46:09.476
- No way.
- I brought you the paper.

46:09.934 --> 46:11.895
They all mention you, look.

46:12.604 --> 46:14.481
- How's it going, Chitoro?
- Careful.

46:15.148 --> 46:16.316
Oh, shit.

46:18.234 --> 46:20.445
Sorry. Look.

46:22.530 --> 46:24.199
Don't get mad.

46:27.076 --> 46:28.369
You're crazy.

46:28.745 --> 46:30.997
You know how hard it was
for me to come?

46:31.372 --> 46:33.416
"Come back, Maradona, we forgive you."

46:34.375 --> 46:35.710
Forgive me for what?

46:39.797 --> 46:45.011
I came here,
where my dad was born, to rest.

46:45.678 --> 46:48.973
It's good that you're getting
some fresh air,

46:49.641 --> 46:51.559
but the fans love you, Diego.

46:51.809 --> 46:53.937
The World Cup's coming up.
They want you there.

46:54.020 --> 46:57.607
They need to understand
that Maradona's not a happiness machine.

47:00.485 --> 47:02.403
I'm just a person.

47:02.487 --> 47:04.906
So now I'll go back to Buenos Aires,

47:04.989 --> 47:08.326
I'll publish that I discovered
your secret place.

47:08.993 --> 47:12.789
And what else do I say?
Give me a scoop, Diego, come on.

47:13.122 --> 47:15.416
I'm tired of people saying
fake things about me.

47:15.542 --> 47:19.170
"Maradona will return to train
for the World Cup in a few days."

47:20.338 --> 47:22.173
I don't know what to tell you.

47:28.429 --> 47:30.932
What are you gonna do?
Hunt and fish?

47:31.724 --> 47:33.726
Give tours on your boat?

47:33.851 --> 47:36.187
- I'll publish that.
- You're clever.

47:36.354 --> 47:40.066
Maybe I could be a singer.
What's so funny?

47:40.149 --> 47:41.901
<i>I loved her, boys</i>

47:42.527 --> 47:43.987
<i>And I love her</i>

47:44.112 --> 47:46.698
<i>And I'll never forget her</i>

47:47.448 --> 47:48.700
I get it.

47:48.783 --> 47:51.452
<i>I get drunk because of her</i>

47:52.120 --> 47:54.872
<i>And who knows what she will do?</i>

47:55.999 --> 47:58.334
You're great... at playing soccer.

47:59.711 --> 48:02.505
- A singer, go figure.
- What are you laughing at?

48:11.598 --> 48:13.516
Where is Maradona?

48:13.600 --> 48:16.060
Has he gone back to his family?

48:16.144 --> 48:18.646
Who will you choose if he won't play?

48:20.315 --> 48:22.400
César, do you know where he is?

48:22.483 --> 48:25.069
Do you have a plan B
if Maradona doesn't come back?

48:31.618 --> 48:33.911
Menotti, what do you know about Diego?

48:34.370 --> 48:36.497
The mystery continues,
where is Maradona?

48:36.581 --> 48:38.458
If I knew, I wouldn't buy this.

48:38.541 --> 48:41.169
Will you play the World Cup
without Maradona?

48:47.550 --> 48:49.260
GOOD NEWS,
WE GOT THE FALKLANDS BACK!

48:49.344 --> 48:52.639
<i>As president of the nation,</i>

48:53.806 --> 48:56.851
<i>I ask the English people</i>
<i>and its government</i>

48:56.934 --> 49:00.104
<i>for restraint in your remarks</i>

49:02.148 --> 49:05.443
<i>and restraint in your actions.</i>

49:06.444 --> 49:08.321
BRITISH HUMILIATED BY THE INVASION

49:08.404 --> 49:10.281
<i>The Argentine government</i>

49:10.365 --> 49:14.327
<i>and its people are</i>
<i>once again becoming enraged</i>

49:14.535 --> 49:19.999
<i>and reporting the greatest offenses.</i>

49:20.375 --> 49:22.710
<i>If they want to come, let them come.</i>

49:22.794 --> 49:24.754
<i>We will bring the battle to them.</i>

49:30.593 --> 49:33.137
Margaret Thatcher
WON'T GRANT SOVEREIGNTY

49:33.221 --> 49:36.849
"Is Galtieri ready to sacrifice
40 thousand lives?" UK Prime Minister

49:36.933 --> 49:41.062
<i>National Radio Buenos Aires,</i>
<i>Argentine Republic,</i>

49:41.145 --> 49:44.732
<i>jointly with LS 82, channel 7,</i>

49:44.816 --> 49:49.320
<i>Argentina, color television,</i>
<i>and all the stations that are part of...</i>

49:58.079 --> 50:01.124
<i>One, two, number 32...</i>

50:05.962 --> 50:07.547
That way, come on.

50:10.633 --> 50:11.843
Guys!

50:16.305 --> 50:18.599
Diego, the president wants to talk to you.

50:31.487 --> 50:33.740
I ask two things of you,

50:34.449 --> 50:39.912
persistence of effort
and a spirit of sacrifice.

50:40.621 --> 50:43.833
In the Falklands, we are winning a war,

50:44.500 --> 50:48.504
but we also have to win
on another battlefield,

50:49.130 --> 50:55.011
so that the world can see
that Argentina is a world power.

50:55.470 --> 50:59.515
You are going to be our soldiers in Spain,

50:59.599 --> 51:04.270
to bring joy
to all the Argentinean people.

51:14.280 --> 51:16.699
<i>Good evening, ladies and gentlemen.</i>

51:16.783 --> 51:20.661
<i>Twenty-four hours</i>

51:20.745 --> 51:22.914
<i>for the Argentine Falklands begins now.</i>

51:23.039 --> 51:25.500
<i>Diego, thank you very much for being here.</i>

51:25.583 --> 51:28.169
<i>Daniel, thank you very much</i>
<i>for being here.</i>

51:28.252 --> 51:29.295
19 HOURS

51:29.378 --> 51:34.425
<i>The national team will donate</i>
<i>100 million pesos.</i>

51:36.886 --> 51:41.641
<i>Having watched</i>
<i>this very moving show yesterday,</i>

51:41.724 --> 51:44.852
<i>I believe that</i>
<i>if we were asked to give our lives,</i>

51:44.936 --> 51:46.729
<i>we would certainly do it.</i>

52:03.162 --> 52:05.832
- Diego! Maradona!
- Maradona, give us a second.

52:05.915 --> 52:07.500
- Diego!
- Diego!

52:13.464 --> 52:15.758
- Diego!
- Maradona!

52:17.343 --> 52:20.054
- Maradona!
- Diego!

52:20.179 --> 52:23.266
- Diego.
- Maradona, one second, please.

52:23.349 --> 52:26.352
Any thoughts about
human rights violations in Argentina?

52:26.435 --> 52:29.647
Do you know that there are thousands
of people who have disappeared?

52:29.730 --> 52:32.692
Argentine soldiers are being massacred
in the war.

52:32.775 --> 52:35.862
Can you play the World Cup
while that's happening, Diego?

52:35.945 --> 52:38.781
It's said that the donations
have never reached the Falklands.

52:38.865 --> 52:41.242
- What do you know about it?
- Diego!

52:42.910 --> 52:44.954
FIFA WORLD CUP
SPAIN - 1982

52:49.750 --> 52:52.587
1982 WORLD CUP OPENING CEREMONY

54:01.030 --> 54:05.451
<i>He shoots... Goal!</i>

54:13.250 --> 54:14.961
Yeah, Diego!

54:35.272 --> 54:38.693
<i>Goal for Belgium! Unbelievable!</i>

54:38.776 --> 54:41.404
<i>Belgium beats Argentina 1-0.</i>

54:41.487 --> 54:45.366
<i>The Belgian forward suddenly appeared</i>
<i>to make the difference.</i>

54:45.449 --> 54:48.411
<i>Argentina loses to Belgium, 1-0.</i>

54:49.620 --> 54:53.332
1982 World Cup: Argentina showed promise
with a champion team,

54:53.457 --> 54:56.961
but won two games and lost three,
saying goodbye in the second phase

54:57.044 --> 54:59.630
with Maradona sent off for a serious foul.

55:01.799 --> 55:04.427
Donations collected during
<i>"24 hours for the Falklands" </i>

55:04.510 --> 55:06.679
never reached their destination.

55:06.846 --> 55:11.434
Many soldiers were sent to war without
training and weapons that didn't work.

55:13.477 --> 55:16.772
After losing the match to Belgium,
Argentina surrendered to the English.

55:16.856 --> 55:19.859
The war left more than
1200 Argentine soldiers wounded

55:19.942 --> 55:21.652
and 649 killed in combat.

55:23.404 --> 55:26.615
A similar number of veterans
committed suicide after the conflict.

55:26.699 --> 55:29.827
The surrender precipitated
the fall of the Military Dictatorship

55:29.910 --> 55:31.662
and the return to democracy.

55:45.634 --> 55:50.473
<i>On behalf of Diego Armando Maradona,</i>
<i>I give you this check.</i>

55:50.556 --> 55:53.851
<i>Gentlemen, a check for 100 million pesos</i>

55:53.934 --> 55:56.645
<i>for the "Argentine Falklands"</i>
<i>patriotic fund</i>

55:56.729 --> 55:58.773
<i>signed by Diego Armando Maradona.</i>

56:30.387 --> 56:34.934
<i>It's really difficult</i>
<i>to leave Argentinos Junior</i>

56:35.017 --> 56:38.562
<i>because I keep it in my heart.</i>
<i>It's part of my life.</i>

57:31.115 --> 57:34.160
<i>You travel to Spain on July 23rd?</i>

57:34.243 --> 57:37.246
<i>Yes, I signed the contract for that date.</i>

57:37.329 --> 57:39.665
<i>-Thank you, Diego, good luck.</i>
<i>-Thank you.</i>
